Skip transfer-kind transactions in AI auto-categorization.

Sure's AI auto-categorizer (Family::AutoCategorizer#scope) queries every
uncategorized, unlocked transaction and sends it to the LLM — including internal
transfers (kind = funds_movement, etc.), which the model then mislabels (e.g. as
"Investment Contributions"). Sure's own model already treats transfers as
non-categorizable (Transfer#categorizable? is false for funds_movement), so
exclude Transaction::TRANSFER_KINDS from the auto-categorization scope. This is
the final gate before the LLM call, so it also covers the rule-executor path.

Optional patch (off by default); enabled per-deployment via patchFlags.
--- a/app/models/family/auto_categorizer.rb
+++ b/app/models/family/auto_categorizer.rb
@@ -90,6 +90,7 @@
 
     def scope
       family.transactions.where(id: transaction_ids, category_id: nil)
+                         .where.not(kind: Transaction::TRANSFER_KINDS)
                          .enrichable(:category_id)
                          .includes(:category, :merchant, :entry)
     end
